wySdrKOdSzo0qiJeEursJT2X5E4B1ffYz0sKxdqVhhZFplJoHgwFUjNmu6jHmO53mw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Java options**\\n\\nI'm considering generating a small helper Java source at test runtime using JavaCompiler from the library package. However, it seems that the compiler isn't available in the native image. I wonder if I could use serialization spoofing to instantiate the inner Slurper without a constructor. I think I need to run a method via the Runnable interface, but the class is package-private. I might try casting the object to Runnable. But then I wonder about using public Java serialization with `ObjectStreamClass`, but that doesn't seem to work either.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating configuration and access**\\n\\nI’m considering if future defaults might allow certain functionalities. The metadata repository includes generated aspects, but we don't commit generated configurations. The agent looks at test reflections to create this configuration. I’m wondering if dynamic access that's tracked includes test reflections too. The coverage report is focusing on the library jar, and it may lead to unnecessary dynamic access. However, since the test's reflection isn't in the library, that seems okay.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ODaLxRHxjEGHSgXnnFZMOrfN|fc_02e6ba7c067c7fd50169efde103db481969dc29e59d2964a56", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge4/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/main/extracted/org/apache/log4j/net/HardenedLoggingEventInputStream.java", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2784, "output": 1686, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24438, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777327607550, "responseId": "resp_02e6ba7c067c7fd50169efddf7fc988196a9cd8bdf859